---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Palindrome Words in Scrabble: KAYAK, LEVEL, CIVIC & More"
  description="Scrabble palindrome words: KAYAK (16), LEVEL (8), CIVIC (12), MADAM (10), REFER (8). Fun vocabulary category with scoring strategy."
  keywords="palindrome scrabble words, kayak scrabble score, level scrabble, civic scrabble word, palindrome word list, scrabble fun words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Palindrome Words in Scrabble: KAYAK, LEVEL, CIVIC & More",
    "description": "Explore palindrome words valid in Scrabble with scores and strategy tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-palindrome-words" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What palindrome words are valid in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Valid Scrabble palindromes include: KAYAK (16pts), CIVIC (12pts), MADAM (10pts), LEVEL (8pts), REFER (8pts), RADAR (6pts), ROTOR (5pts), TENET (5pts), DEIFIED (12pts), and RACECAR (11pts). These read the same forwards and backwards." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the highest-scoring palindrome in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "KAYAK scores 16 points (K=5, A=1, Y=4, A=1, K=5) making it the highest-scoring common palindrome. With the double K tiles, it benefits greatly from premium squares — K on a DL square adds 5 extra points." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Are palindromes strategically useful in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Palindromes have mixed strategic value. KAYAK and CIVIC score well due to high-value letters. LEVEL and REFER are useful for their common tiles. The main advantage is memorability — palindromes are easy to recall under time pressure because of their distinctive pattern." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Palindrome Words in Scrabble: KAYAK, LEVEL & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Palindromes — words that read the same forwards and backwards — are among Scrabble's most memorable vocabulary. From KAYAK's 16 points to the humble ROTOR, these symmetrical words are easy to recall under tournament pressure and several pack serious scoring punch.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Palindrome</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KAYAK — 16 points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">K(5) + A(1) + Y(4) + A(1) + K(5) = 16 base points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Two K tiles (5pts each) plus a Y (4pts) make KAYAK the highest-scoring common palindrome. Place either K on a DL square for 21 points. On a TW square row, it can hit 48.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">All Valid Palindromes</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KAYAK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CIVIC</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MADAM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LEVEL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">REFER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RADAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ROTOR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TENET</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Palindromes by Length</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">3 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">EYE (6) · ERE (3) · EWE (6) · AHA (6) · ANA (3) · BIB (7) · BOB (7) · DAD (5) · DID (5) · GAG (5) · MOM (7) · MUM (7) · NUN (3) · POP (7) · PUP (7) · SIS (3) · TAT (3) · TIT (3) · TOT (3)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">5+ Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KAYAK (16) · CIVIC (12) · MADAM (10) · LEVEL (8) · REFER (8) · RADAR (6) · ROTOR (5) · TENET (5) · DEIFIED (12) · RACECAR (11) · REVIVER (12)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Value</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Easy recall under pressure:</span> Palindromes stick in memory because of their symmetric pattern. In timed tournament play, they come to mind faster than irregular words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Duplicate letter advantage:</span> KAYAK uses 2 K tiles, LEVEL uses 2 L tiles. If you draw duplicate letters, palindromes are one of the few word categories that actively use them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CIVIC and KAYAK score well:</span> Both contain high-value tiles (C=3, K=5, Y=4). They outperform many common 5-letter words and do not require rare tiles from the bag.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Fun Fact</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">DEIFIED (12pts) and RACECAR (11pts) are 7-letter palindromes — <span class="text-white font-medium">they qualify for the bingo bonus</span>. A DEIFIED bingo scores 62 points. A RACECAR bingo scores 61 points. Rare but spectacular.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/palindrome-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Palindrome Words in Scrabble: Full Analysis</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-double-letters/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Double Letters in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/weird-scrabble-facts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Weird Scrabble Facts You Didn't Know</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any palindrome's validity — instant, free, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
